body.description: Turns so you don’t have to twist! The Graco® Turn2Me™ 3-in-1 Car Seat rotates from rear-facing for a face-to-face connection with baby to get them in and out of the car with ease! You'll hear it "click" back into position for a safe and comfy ride. This 3-in-1 car seat from the most loved gear brand* features 3 modes of use to grow with your child—from 4-100 lb! The No-Rethread Simply Safe Adjust™ Harness System allows you to adjust the height of the 10-position headrest and harness in one motion for just the right fit. Our easy installation SnugLock® technology works in rear- and forward-facing modes to get your seat installed in less than one minute. We included our push-button InRight™ LATCH, which provides an easy, one-second attachment with an audible click to help ensure secure installation. The easy-to-read level indicator helps to eliminate installation guesswork, and the 4-position recline smoothly adjusts to help with installation and keeps your child comfy. The 2 easy-to-clean cup holders keep your child's drinks and snacks close at hand. Plush infant inserts help to keep your infant feeling cradled and comfortable. A steel-reinforced frame provides strength and durability for years of use. The car seat is Graco® ProtectPlus Engineered™ to help protect in frontal, side, rear, and rollover crashes. *based on Brand Preceptor 2020

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely love this
reviews.reviewText: After watching a short video from Graco on how to install the car seat, it was really easy to install. I was a little intimidated at first because I did hear some reviews that they couldn’t get it installed into a small car or that it did slide, but I had no issues. It was super easy, and it fits wonderful in my car. I also love how it swivels and it makes my baby so happy, and myself when getting her in and out. Baby is happy with how comfortable it is as well and has great padding. Cup holders are a plus, since my old Graco didn’t have those before. Definitely an upgrade and worth the purchase since it can grow with them as they grow. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this car seat! The quality is amazing, per usual with Graco. The turning feature is an absolute game-changer and will save your back! I am 6 months pregnant with an 18-month-old, and this is the BEST purchase I've made, by far!!The fabric is SO easy to clean with a vacuum and damp cloth, but also easy to remove and reinstall if you want to throw it into the washer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install if you watch the YouTube video
reviews.reviewText: Life changing! I’m a small person with a larger car and I’d tweak my back putting my baby in our previous car seat. I had also accidentally hit my sons head on the car roof/door jam in my struggle to get him as he got heavier and wigglier it was just too hard to get him over the side of the seat and situated. I got this one obviously since turns facing towards you so you plop them in really easy. I don’t have to fight him anymore it is soooo worth the money. The other seat he would arch and I would struggle to get his butt in the right spot. The one handed lever under the cup holder makes it super easy to unlock and swivel this seat. It also has nice padding and easy to remove if there’s spill/vomit. The other thing we realized right away is that it somehow has a smaller profile leaving enough room for my husband to sit in-front of the car seat with plenty of leg room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the Money But...
reviews.reviewText: This carseat is seriously genius. We've been using it for about a month now. we have a larger truck with no running boards so putting the baby in her seat was a chore every.single.time. Being able to turn the seat, put her in, buckle her, and then turn it back is such a back saver and eases the frustration of trying to wrangle a child into a seat sideways. There is so much cushioning she seriously falls asleep in it every time we go somewhere. I also want to commend the anchor system. Her carseat before this one had the original "C"-like clamps on them that were a pain in the butt to attach and detach. These just pop right in and have a button to release the hooks allowing them to just pull straight out. Some cars still give me troubles when hooking it in but its the vehicle not the seat.Something I do want to point out is the seat gets very hot when the child is in it. Our particular car doesn't have any ceiling vents for the back seats (she is rear-facing) and in the hotter months she was drenched in sweat when I would get her out of the seat because all of the cushioning is just so hot-- comfortable, but hot.Another thing I would like to add is that this thing is BIG and HEAVY. Now hopefully you aren't having to move it back and forth to much but Lord, if you do... overall though the benefits of the swiveling and easy use of the seat far outweigh the 2 inconveniences I have found with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Game-Changer - Compact and Swift Rotating Car Seat
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This rotating car seat has truly been a game-changer in our family's life, and I can't help but sing its praises.First and foremost, it's not too big and clunky, which sets it apart from many other rotating car seats on the market. Its design strikes the perfect balance between functionality and space-saving. You don't feel like it's eating up extra room in your vehicle, making it ideal for smaller cars or families with multiple car seats.The standout feature of this car seat is the swift, one-handed operation to rotate it. This innovation has made loading and unloading our baby a breeze. No more awkward contortions or struggling to reach into the car – a simple, smooth turn and you're good to go. It's a real time-saver, especially for busy parents.My baby absolutely loves it too. I can see the delight on his face when putting him in it for car rides. This car seat is not only safe but also comfortable and enjoyable for him, which is a huge win.Another impressive aspect is the envy it has stirred among other moms. Every mom who has seen it can't help but express their jealousy at not having discovered it sooner. It's a testament to its uniqueness and practicality.In summary, this rotating car seat has made our life easier in so many ways. It's compact, easy to operate with one hand, and our baby adores it. It's the envy of fellow moms, and I couldn't recommend it more. It has become an essential part of our family's travel routine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Comfy and convenient, cheap fabric
reviews.reviewText: Love the one hand rotation, cup holders, it’s comfy and roomy for the baby and not to bulky in the car. So these features just outweigh the major downside as cheap fabric, not able to change the recline position when installed. I Hate the fabric (too cheap) and instructions (I’m engineer and spent 15 minutes just figuring them out), hate that I cannot change recline position in rear-seating position without adjusting the latch belt (it blocks the seat ability to recline because of the how it realized in the base). Why Graco cannot do the rigid-latch and provide better fabric in their seats? They all are looking cheap and shabby after some use, also why does it have fire-retardant fabric in relatively expensive model?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I recently bought this car seat and am thrilled with its design, installation ease, and safety features. The sleek, durable construction caught my eye, and the adjustable straps ensured a secure fit for my child.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this car seat
reviews.reviewText: I love this car seat! The color is beautiful! Would absolutely purchase again. Some things to point out are: heavy as can be, has lots of cushion and nice feeling material vs some of the other models/brands, only turns when rear facing, I can not get the cup holders to stay in place but maybe I’m not snapping them in all the way? I don’t find those as cons and loved it so much we bought another for our new grand baby.
